value.value: An angiosarcoma that is located_in the aorta.
An angiosarcoma and sarcoma of breast and vascular neoplasm of breast that is located_in the cells that line the blood vessels within the breast or underarm area.
An angiosarcoma and gallbladder sarcoma that is located_in the gallbladder.
A thyroid sarcoma and angiosarcoma that results_in a high prevalence of iodine-deficient goiter.
A thyroid gland cancer that is located_in the supporting cells of the thyroid.

An angiosarcoma and hemangioma of skin and malignant skin vascular tumor and sarcoma of skin that is located_in the skin and results_in an enlarged bruise (a blue-black nodule) and an unhealed ulceration.
A gastrointestinal system benign neoplasm that is a located_in the salivary glands.
A cervix endometrical stromal tumor that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from embryonic mesoderm.
A cervical cancer that derives_from the fibrous connective tissue of the endometrium.
An angiosarcoma and sarcoma of prostate that is located_in the prostate.
An angiosarcoma and sarcoma of the mediastinum that is located_in the mediastinum.
An ovary sarcoma that is a malignant vascular tumor that derives_from blood vessels.
A carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of cuboidal mucous cells, goblet-like mucous cells, squamoid cells, cystic changes, and a fibrotic stromal formation.
A syndrome that affects growth, cranial development, hair growth and dental development.

A hair disease that is characterized by sparse hair on the scalp resulting from abnormal hair follicle development and has_material_basis_in mutations in proteins involved in hair growth, division or proliferation of cells within hair follicles.
A writing disorder that involves a deficiency in the ability to write where the writing is distorted or incorrect, spelling difficulty, poor handwriting or trouble putting thoughts on paper.
An agnosia that involves a severe problem with recalling words or names.
An amnestic disorder that involves a loss of one's pre-existing memories to conscious recollection.
An adult sarcoma of soft tissue and mesenchymal chondrosarcoma that is located_in the cartilage.
A chondrosarcoma that is located_in exclusively soft tissue and that is characterized by the presence of chondroblast-like cells in a myxoid stroma and a multinodular growth pattern.
A carcinoma that is composed of large, monotonous rounded or overtly polygonal-shaped cells with abundant cytoplasm.

An ovarian carcinoma that is characterized by large pleiomorphic cells with large round or oval nuclei, presence of mitoses and staining for neuroendocrine (NE) markers and has_material_basis_in neuroendocrine cells.

A mouth disease that is characterized by the presence of filmy opalescence of the mucosa in the early stages to a whitish gray cast with a coarsely wrinkled surface in the later stages, associated with intracellular edema of the spinous or malpighian layer.

A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine with the nematode Ascaris lumbricoides. Larvae migrating through the lungs cause cough, wheezing and hemoptysis. Bowel or biliary obstruction causes cramping abdominal pain, nausea, and vomiting. Peritonitis, enlargement of the liver or spleen, toxicity and pneumonia are observed when larvae get into the portal circulation.
An endometritis that is present for weeks or more and does not have an identifiable causative organism.
An endometritis that is characterized by the presence of granulomas in the uterus.
An ichthyosis that is characterized by generalized erythema, skin blisters and skin fragility, manifested at birth.
A biliary tract cancer that is located_in the bile duct.
A hepatobiliary system cancer that results_in malignant growth located_in the gallbladder or located_in the bile duct.
